    "is_good_patch": true,
    "synth_pr": "\n## Title: Fix signed/unsigned integer comparison in RA scheduler\n\n### Summary\nThe `check_Msg4_retransmission` function in the eNB random access scheduler contained a signed/unsigned integer comparison that could lead to incorrect HARQ retransmission handling. The local variable `round` was declared as `int` but assigned from `UE_sched_ctrl[UE_id].round[CC_idP][harq_pid]` which is of type `uint8_t`. When comparing `round != 8` and `round > 0`, this mismatch could cause unexpected behavior in certain compiler configurations.\n\nThe issue manifested as missed Msg4 retransmissions during RRC connection establishment, particularly when UEs experienced poor channel conditions requiring multiple HARQ rounds. Some UEs would fail to complete the connection setup procedure and timeout.\n\nThe fix changes the declaration of `round` from `int` to `uint8_t` to match the source data type, eliminating the signed/unsigned comparison warnings and ensuring correct behavior.\n\n### Changes\n- `openair2/LAYER2/MAC/eNB_scheduler_RA.c`: Changed `int round;` to `uint8_t round;` in `check_Msg4_retransmission` function to match the source data type from `UE_sched_ctrl.round` array.\n\n"
}